      <item>
        <title>Change canonical links from head_tags</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[SantosGuillamot]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/modyydom">@modyydom</a>!</p>
<p>The <code>@frontity/head-tags</code> package uses the <code>url</code> defined at <code>state.frontity.url</code> in your <code>frontity.settings.js</code>. It seems that there you have set your backend domain, and you should use your Frontity domain.</p>
<p>Could you confirm if that’s the case?</p>
<p>This package hasn’t settings, but you must defined two parameters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<code>state.frontity.url</code> : Usually defined at <code>frontity.settngs.js</code> file. (the url of your site)</li>
<li>
<code>state.source.api</code> : Defined at <code>@frontity/wp-source</code> inside <code>frontity.settings.js</code> file (the api where your project is pointing)</li>
</ul>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/change-canonical-links-from-head-tags/1154/2">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
